To use the code, download the controller.py file into the Comma AI /Controllers 
subfolder. All other files should be placed directly into the main Comma AI file directory. 
Although a baseline K matrix is already given (offline trained), this may be re-created with the command:

python train_fourier_koopman.py

After the baseline Koopman matrix has been generated, the custom Comma AI evaluation function 
may be executed from the main directory using the following command:

python eval.py \
   --model_path ./models/tinyphysics.onnx \
   --data_path ./data \
   --num_segs 100 \
   --test_controller controller \
   --baseline_controller pid

This will generate the Comma AI report in the main directory as an HTML file, 
which may then be opened and evaluated.

If a single run is needed, rather than the full evaluation pipeline, the simple:

    python plot_tisac.py

may be used to run the controller on a single data set (selectable within the code) 
and to evaluate the controllers performance on that specific segment.

Any further questions regarding usage of the code should be directed to Alex.
